          "title": "Load Capacity Units (LCUs)",
          "description": "An LCU measures the dimensions on which the Gateway Load Balancer processes your traffic (averaged over an hour).",
          "bodyText": "Please specify at least one of the following dimensions to determine LCU pricing.",
          "helpText": "An LCU measures the dimensions on which the Gateway Load Balancer processes your traffic (averaged over an hour). The three dimensions measured are: new connections or flows, active connections or flows, and bandwidth. You are charged only on one of the three dimensions that has the highest usage for the hour.",
          "helpUrl": {
            "$LINK": {
              "type": "pricing",
              "path": "/elasticloadbalancing/pricing/"
            }
          },
